{
  "texts": [
    "By handling repetitive tasks, these models can free up human workers to focus on tasks requiring creativity, empathy, and nuanced understanding [67,68].",
    "Responsible development entails fostering dialogue on the economic impact and implementing strategies to adapt the workforce to technological changes.",
    "This may involve reskilling programs, creating new roles that leverage AI, or implementing policies to mitigate negative impacts on employment.",
    "Promoting Accessibility and Mitigating the Digital DivideThe development and training of large language models require significant computational resources, potentially widening the digital gap between well-resourced companies and others [69][70].",
    "Advocating for responsible AI democratization efforts is crucial to prevent these technologies from serving only a privileged few [65,68]."
  ]
}